How to run the app-bench.sh benchmark:

  1. Make a copy of the fscq repo, without doc or wiki, and make a
     fresh git commit, placing the resulting repo in /tmp/fscq-clean.

  FSCQ

    cd ../src
    dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/sda3 bs=4096 count=34310
    ./mkfs /dev/sda3
    ./fuse /dev/sda3 -s -f /tmp/ft

    script app-bench-fscq.out -c './app-bench.sh /tmp/fscq-clean /tmp/ft'

  xv6

    cd ../xv6
    ./mkfs /dev/sda3
    ./xv6fs /dev/sda3 -s -f /tmp/ft

    script app-bench-xv6.out -c './app-bench.sh /tmp/fscq-clean /tmp/ft'

  Linux

    mke2fs -j /dev/sda3
    mount /dev/sda3 /tmp/ft -o data=journal,sync
    chmod 777 /tmp/ft

    script app-bench-ext3.out -c './app-bench.sh /tmp/fscq-clean /tmp/ft'
